{ By Reuters   Published:  07:52, 13 February 2020   https://www.dailymail.co.uk//wires/reuters/article-7999015/PRESS-DIGEST--Bulgaria--Feb-13.html }
SOFIA, Feb 13 (Reuters) - These are some of the main stories in Bulgarian newspapers on Thursday. Reuters has not verified these stories and does not vouch for their accuracy. -- Chief Prosecutor Ivan Geshev has instructed the State Agency for National Security to carry out a full review of the entire privatisation process during the country´s transition from communism to democracy, the prosecutors' office said (24 Chasa, Trud, Monitor, Duma) -- Bulgaria's government will provide funds to buy voting machines so that there is one at each polling station at the next elections, Prime Minister Boyko Borissov said (24 Chasa, Duma, Trud) -- Scientific comparative analysis of food and beverages of the same brands sold in Bulgaria and elsewhere in the European Union has established only a few minimal differences, the Consumer Protection Commission said (Trud, Monitor) -- Bulgaria´s parliament will vote the second reading of amendments to legislation related to the Brexit withdrawal agreement in February, allowing British citizens living in Bulgaria to use personal ID issued by the Bulgarian authorities for a year after the end of the transition period, after which they will require new personal documents (Monitor, Trud) 
